## Project Identity
- Name: IEEPIS (ICT Equipment and Employee Profile Information System)
- Purpose: DepEd Philippines school-division ICT inventory management
- Stack: PHP 8.4 / Laravel 11 / FilamentPHP v3 / Livewire v3 / MySQL 8 / Tailwind v3
- Dev Environment: Laravel Sail (Docker)

## Mandatory Rules

1. ALL commands use `vendor/bin/sail` prefix — never bare `php` or `composer` directly.
2. NEVER add `employee_id` FK to the `equipment` table. Accountability is tracked via `equipment_assignments`.
3. Core models (School, Employee, Equipment, Document, Ticket) use soft deletes — never hard delete.
4. Only ONE active assignment per equipment — enforced in `EquipmentAssignment` model.
5. `school_admin` role → restricted to their school by a global Eloquent scope. Never bypass.
6. After every PHP change: `vendor/bin/sail bin pint --dirty --format agent`
7. Write PHPUnit class-based tests — never Pest.
8. Before writing Filament code: use MCP `search-docs` tool.

